76561198047169453,Recommended,258010,22226562,"Posted: 3 April, 2016",all,DeinonychusCowboy,"A quirky space shooter with a deeply developed universe and a LOT of satire. A space comedy, but the plot grows surprisingly deep and involved over time. Think Hitchhiker's Guide in tone, though the execution is rather different.Gameplay is good once you get used to the controls, but there are several different control schemes, so you can find the one that is most intuitive for you. Missions are short and to the point, which works very well given the game doesn't take itself seriously (a good thing).Ships are extremely customizable, to the point of being confusing and unwieldy. To do an effective build,  you'll have to spend several hours learning about the ship types and components and how they work. Or you can just slap a bunch of random crap into a Caster and mash buttons, like I did. A great deal of potential for novel/interesting playstyles with this system, but very little hand-holding for players who just want progressively better ships to shoot at the bad guys with.Well-balanced and always remains interesting. The plot moves forward more steadily and naturally than many games I've played. Characters are loveable, though the game has a tendency of killing them off, so don't get too attached.Graphics, while nothing spectacular, stand out nicely among your usual indie games."
