76561198066709775,Recommended,258010,19560418,"Posted: 7 December, 2015",all,skywill_15,"This is a great game.  The writing is brilliant, the science fiction as inventive as you can find anywhere while still making physicists like me happy.  You will find more witty one liners and past culture references than you can shake a stick at.  It has several multiplayer modes as diverse and almost as balanced as League of Legends, and I do not say that lightly.  It has a bunch of ATARI games you can play, and everything you do unlocks more of the game.  It just keeps unfolding like a great book.  The campaign introduces you gently to the many possible tactics in the game.  The setting is fantastic.  Ring Runner is clearly a labor of love; you will find it in every nook and cranny.It is the best game you will buy this year."
