,Recommended,258010,10262370,"Posted: 28 May, 2014",all,Mazzle Dazzle,"I bought this game for one reason, duo ships for local co-op(I researched local co-op and tried to figure out how before I bought it).  What I discovered was an amazing game.  The premise of the game is awesome.  I also like the humor of the game.  For one you have a universal translator thing but it's like a real translator as it translates things literally and you have to use context clues to figure out what the real meaning behind it is. It's kind of a joke but I thought it was hilarious as someone that has attempted to learn another language.Anyway there is such a large variety of ships and a lot of subsystems that can really add a lot of depth to the game.  For instance you can take a ship and have the worst heatsink in the world on it, but you can add a vent thing that reduces your heat by venting it out leaving a flaming trail that will hurt other ships.  You can put a stealth system and mark targets before unleashing a payload that will kill most ships.  You can lay turrets or summon assisting drone ships that you can command.The ship customization adds a huge level of depth and you can use moves creatively.  For instance you could use a turret and a tether and drag the turret with you as a side weapon, you could drop an explosive and use a kinetic push move to launch it at someone.  That's just the tip of it.If you have any doubts try the demo and I'm sure you'll love it."
