,Not Recommended,258010,9874586,"Posted: 19 April, 2014",all,TreebearZ,"In an era of gaming where procedural generation has become the hallmark of most indie game design, Ring Runner opts for a more traditional RPG style.  Unfortunately, the game design in this title feels as archaic as its graphical style.  The player is presented with a story-driven quest that has you hoping between maps of varying size, completing the objectives of said quest, and then hopping off to the next map.  Every experience you have on a map is very compartmentalized, so much so that after an hour of play, I felt like the game was still in a tutorial state.  I was waiting for the moment where the game would let you loose and explore the galaxy on your own terms, to no avail.If you are looking for a more open-ended space-themed ARPG, check out the vastly superior SPAZ."
