76561198056325899,Recommended,258010,17385086,"Posted: 4 August, 2015",all,Snowfallgamer,"Ring Runner Flight of the Sages (RR) is a top down shooter with a complementary customization system at it's core.The skeleton of the game is simple to play, pair this with enough customization options to keep you trying something new and you've got a recipie for addiction.TL:DRSingle player:The game starts off slow so you can get used to the flow. The first missions (or tutorial galaxy) starts you off escaping a medical facility with a portion of your brain removed to fit in a neuro hud that talks to you with it's own personality. Afterwards you'll begin to meet locals of the scrapyard you've stumbled into and the rollercoaster begins. Fight for survival, get takin in as a gladiator and get caught in a feud between 2 clans vying for control of the sector.sounds pretty straight forward right?well after the tutorial galaxy is complete it's time to learn what makes RR such a great game.-You're given access to the customization system so you can play the game with whatever fitting you want(light fighter, Heavy weapons ship or a cloaking gravity manipulator that destroys other ships by smashing them against debries. It actually gets crazier than that)-you get to choose what missions you complete in what order so it is less linear-The missions themselves have a great deal of humor in them(build a shrine to a space flail for a mercenary that tried to kill you)(Raid a bank with a garbage truck)(Turn a circus into a gladitorial combat arena)(and Many others)Multiplayer-The game offers a few game modes for MP which are great when you have a few friends to game with.these include:Hoard / zombie survivalMobaDeath Match-There is a small community left however it's not entirely active. For those who are active they're actually really hard to compete with. So i'd reccomend you buy the game with friends if you're interested in MP shenanigens.TL:DRSingleplayer: The bread and butter of the game. Has great humor, Linear but gives you mission selection to complete as you want and stays fresh throughout.Multiplayer: Great with friends boring withoutCustomization: You constantly unlock new things as you play so you'll always be trying something new."
