76561197998167902,Recommended,258010,14928242,"Posted: 16 March, 2015",all,Suslik,"Short versionJesus christ. The game is ridiculously, overwhelmingly awesome.Longer versionCombat:Gratitious Space Battles combat was dull. SPAZ combat was fun. Reassembly combat is great. Ring Runner's combat is just outstanding. It's super dynamic, fast-paced but not chaotic: you control the pace of fight. It's like an action-RPG with a very deep skill system, where every skill is indeed unique. Most abilities have very low cooldowns, so you'll have to blink, dodge, slow time, push, pull, manage your heat, shield and energy and destroy your enemies in any way you can imagine. 10/10.Customization:No, you can not build your ship from scratch like you can in reassembly. But hell, this game's customization system is just way more advanced and balanced! Every hull has a set number of mounting points for different types of devices. Every mounting point has a capacity: the more capacity it has, the more comlex gear you may equip to it grating you passive bonuses or active abilities. You may equip multiple devices into a single mounting point if you have the capacity. It's so way better than in any other seemengly similar game like Gratitious Space Battles or SPAZ.10/10.Abilities:Basically everything including evasion and weapon autofiring is an ability in this game. And wow, varied they are. Abilities are designed to be very synergetic and they often let you turn your downsides into an advantage. For example you can grab a super-powerful engine that generates a ton of heat. Overheating is generally not the thing you want. But you can attach a freaking molten laser that dissipates all your heat in one shot if you're overheated! Or you can equip an engine with high top speed but low acceleration and get an ability that instantly accelerates you to maximum speed in any direction.Basically there are only 2 games I know that have as synergetic abilities as this: Tales of Maj'Eyal 4 and Baldur's Gate 2(wizard). Please tell me if you know another!10/10 here, no doubtGraphics:The game is developed by one family. Graphics are 3d while game mechanics are 2d. They pretty advanced, run smoothly but I personally am not a huge fan of this game's graphical content. SPAZ or Gratitious Space Battles look better if you ask me. But it's nowhere close to being game-breaking or unlikable.7/10Story:I have not completed the story yet. So far(10 hours of story) it is pretty fun and well-written. It's not a Planescape: Torment in space but there's a decent sci-fi story that utilizes some very well-though physical concepts. Like Mass Effect is based on physical phenomon called Mass Effect(some materials may change their density when electrical current is applied to them) this game has numerous concepts that I found even more interesting(physics is my major).8/10(?)Music:Game's music is atmospheric enough and fits it well though it it sometimes a little repititive. You're unlikely to listen to game's OST when you're not playing like you listen to Silent HIll's or Final Fantasy's but it is a great soundtrack and you won't end up listening to your own music instead of built-in soundtrack.7/10Controls:As I said before, most abilities have low cooldowns and you may end up equipping a lot of them. Ability management, movement, evasion and heat/energy/ammo may will be as challenging as you want them to. If you can't handle too much active abilities, equip passives instead. But I love controlling as much as my brain can handle and the game certainly gives me opportunity to equip enough active skills. My gamepad acts funny with this game(analog joystick sticks to 8 discrete directions)  but controlling with mouse + keyboard is great anyway and controlling multiple skills is more convinient with keyboard.General impression:The game is Loved by its developers. You can feel it in every aspect in every small detail. It's like the opposite to stuff you see in android market or most early access garbage that are developed to get as much money and as soon is possible. This game is so detailed, so well-though, so *lived* by it's developers I just can't help but admire it. It's very strange and disappointing to see how unknown it is and it's 75/100 metascore rating is just frustrating. Do not let AAA-crap reviwers fool you, this is a true indie game gem."
