,Recommended,258010,19592799,"Posted: 9 December, 2015",all,Fou Lou,"Incredible Hidden gem. If you like Top down space games with Newtonian Physics Flight model its a must have. The price is quite awesome for that amount of content that is offered and for me most aspects of the game felt quite fleshed out and polished. The story took me about 20 hours.Oh and theres a demo. Try that if the reviews arent convincing.Longer Review:Story and missions:Since its Story driven there is no open world. You have a Galaxy map to choose between Mission arcs after the Introduction. Each mission arc is a little side story in itself for example agressivle selling DOVRAK keyboard or Planning a heist.The Story is in my opionion well written and engaging. It has some memorable characters in it and it doesnt take itself too seriously. Its kinda a wacky universe but without being silly. Indruduction and tutorial is woven into the story in a beliveable way. And i got the feeling of ""just on more mission i want to see what happens next"".The missions themselves reach from very short to quite a bit longer and are really varied. Just a excerpt of what types i have encountered: gladiator style where you fight in a arena agains other ships, racing missions with weapons on a track, tower defense missions, stealth missions and the obligatory fly around and kill stuff including whole starbases missions.Besides that you have scenarios. like a dotastyle game, zombie survival, deathmatch and so on.And the rostrum acade with some minigames that will remind you of arace classicsgamepalay:Its a newtonian Style shooter. So no strafing and backwarts. Just forward turn and brakes. But youll get pretty fast used to it. But there lots of movmentbased abillitys that can fling you and/or your enemys around.The ship archetypes allow very different styles of gameplay. Rogues feel like snipers, Casters have flashy AOE abiitys, Fighters like dogfighting and so on.Besides that you have tons of different ships and lots of sidegrades at tier5 that mix up the archetypes and with tons of equipment which is unlocked via research or missions there is such room for customization and trying new things.The resrach system is quite awesome and allows to unlock up to 10 items (or get money) when youre not playing the game. And ingame money earned while playing speed the research up. Though you cant research a specific ithem directly. Its devided into different categorys which represent the equipmentnodes of the different ships.Its not a RPG in the classical sense though. Because there is no leveling. Everything is unlocked via Story, research or funds.Asthetics are fitting and feel quite unique. Because its 2.5d it is clearly visible where you can actually fly against something and where you can fly freely. The feels a bit gamey but doesnt disctract from the immersion too much.For me it is a really great game and it is sad that it had such a bad launch date and kinda slipped under the radar. This game deserves more than it actually got."
